# Frontend Development Guidelines

## Architecture

The frontend uses vanilla HTML/CSS/JavaScript for maximum compatibility with hospital systems:

- **Main Chat**: [frontend/index.html](mdc:frontend/index.html) - Primary chat interface
- **Selection**: [frontend/select.html](mdc:frontend/select.html) - Chatbot selection page
- **Admin**: [frontend/admin.html](mdc:frontend/admin.html) - Management interface
- **Styling**: [frontend/style.css](mdc:frontend/style.css) - Responsive healthcare UI
- **Widget**: [frontend/widget/](mdc:frontend/widget/) - Embeddable components

## Healthcare UI Standards

- **Accessibility**: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance for hospital staff
- **Responsive Design**: Works on desktop, tablet, and mobile devices
- **High Contrast**: Clear visibility in hospital lighting conditions
- **Touch-Friendly**: Large touch targets for mobile use
- **Error Prevention**: Clear validation and confirmation dialogs

## JavaScript Guidelines

- Use vanilla JavaScript for maximum hospital system compatibility
- Implement proper error handling for network issues
- Use async/await for API calls with loading states
- Include comprehensive logging for troubleshooting
- Follow healthcare IT naming conventions

## CSS Standards

- Use CSS Grid and Flexbox for responsive layouts
- Implement consistent spacing and typography
- Use semantic color names for healthcare contexts
- Ensure proper focus states for accessibility
- Test across different screen sizes and browsers

## Widget Development

- Create embeddable components for hospital systems
- Use iframe-safe communication patterns
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Ensure consistent styling across different contexts
- Provide clear documentation for hospital IT teams

## Performance Considerations

- Minimize bundle size for hospital network constraints
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Use lazy loading for non-critical resources
- Optimize for slower hospital network connections
- Test performance on various hospital devices
